database.name: MetabolomicsWorkbench
database.description: The Metabolomics Workbench will serve as a national and international repository for metabolomics data and metadata and will provide analysis tools and access to metabolite standards, protocols, tutorials, training, and more.

entry.name: Rat HCR/LCR Stamina Study
entry.description: To determine the basis of running capacity and health differences in outbread male N/NIH rats selected for high capacity (HCR) and low capacity (LCR) running (a surrogate for VO2max) (see:Science. 2005 Jan 21;307(5708):418-20). Plasma collected at 12 months of age in generation 28 rats after ad lib feeding or 40% caloric restriction beginning at week 8 of age. All animals fasted 4 hours prior to collection between 5-8 pm.
